Example \(\PageIndex{8b}\) Solve the problem above by rewriting before taking the log. Solution Starting at the equation \[38.8(1.0264)^{t} =41.3(1.0224)^{t}
onumber\] Divide to move the exponential terms to one side of the equation and the constants to the other side \[\dfrac{1.0264^{t} }{1.0224^{t} } =\dfrac{41.3}{38.8}
onumber\] Using exponent rules to group on the left, \[\left(\dfrac{1.0264}{1.0224} ight)^{t} =\dfrac{41.3}{38.8}
onumber\] Taking the log of both sides \[\log \left(\left(\dfrac{1.0264}{1.0224} ight)^{t} ight)=\log \left(\dfrac{41.3}{38.8} ight)
onumber\] Utilizing the exponent property on the left, \[t\log \left(\dfrac{1.0264}{1.0224} ight)=\log \left(\dfrac{41.3}{38.8} ight)
onumber\] Dividing gives \[t=\dfrac{\log \left(\dfrac{41.3}{38.8} ight)}{\log \left(\dfrac{1.0264}{1.0224} ight)} \approx 15.991	ext{ years}
onumber\] While the answer does not immediately appear identical to that produced using the previous method, note that by using the difference property of logs, the answer could be rewritten: \[t=\dfrac{\log \left(\dfrac{41.3}{38.8} ight)}{\log \left(\dfrac{1.0264}{1.0224} ight)} =\dfrac{\log (41.3)-\log (38.8)}{\log (1.0264)-\log (1.0224)}
onumber\]

